CLASSICAL SWINE FEVER - COSTA RICA (02)
***************************************
A ProMED-mail post
Date: Fri, 5 Sep 1997
From: Dorothy Preslar <dpreslar@fas.org>
Source: OIE Disease Information, Vol. 10, No. 36

Follow-up report No. 1: Translation of a fax received on 2 September 1997
from Dr J.F. Coronado Faith, Director of Animal Health, Ministry of
Agriculture and Animal Husbandry, San Jose.
End of previous report period: 22 August 1997. End of this report period: 1
September 1997.
New outbreaks:
Location No. of outbreaks
Upala canton, Alajuela province 2
Total number of outbreaks identified since 1 January 1997: seven (7).
Description of affected population in the new outbreaks: adult sows.
Total number of animals in the new outbreaks:
susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
4 2 0 4 0
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: National Veterinary Services
Laboratory (LANASEVE).

B. Diagnostic tests used: serological (ELISA) and immunohistochemical
(abidin-biotin stain and alkaline phosphatase).
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: the source was probably an
infected pig introduced from a neighbouring country.
B. Mode of spread: direct transmission.
Control measures during reporting period: stamping-out; quarantine measures
and movement control inside the country; control programme for the whole
country.
.....................................dp/jpw
